featureDescription.name: id
featureDescription.description: Integer ID of this record in the GeoNames database.

featureDescription.name: name
featureDescription.description: Canonical name of this record, usually an English one.

featureDescription.name: featureClass
featureDescription.description: Single character feature class, see: http://www.geonames.org/export/codes.html

featureDescription.name: adm1
featureDescription.description: The code for top level administrative division, most of which are FIPS codes. ISO codes are used for US, CH, BE and ME. UK and Greece are using an additional level between country and fips code. The code '00' stands for general features where no specific adm1 code is defined.

featureDescription.name: adm2
featureDescription.description: The code for the second level administrative division, i.e. a county in the US.

featureDescription.name: adm3
featureDescription.description: The code for third level administrative division.

featureDescription.name: adm4
featureDescription.description: The code for fourth level administrative division.

featureDescription.name: latitude
featureDescription.description: Latitude as a 32-bit floating point number.

featureDescription.name: longitude
featureDescription.description: Longitude as a 32-bit floating point number.

featureDescription.name: elevation
featureDescription.description: Elevation in meters above/below normal as a 16-bit signed integer number; optional, defaults to 0.
